      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RUGGED ETHICS (2) scored two back in the quickest time on the program then drifted back and missed the frame latest finishing a 1.5 lengths 4th at Wentworth Park (29.96). Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings six times from 12 attempts. Should be very hard to beat this time. SOVEREIGN REIGN (1) stalked the lead after a clean break from the tricky draw and went on to finish third (24.90) at Goulburn in a Grade 4/5 over 440m. Won at his only start from this box. Winning chance. ALAKAZAM (8) ran below his best last time finishing eighth (42.62) over 720m at Wentworth Park in a NG. Has a good record at this journey. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from four starts. Can figure in the finish. TRUNKEY VILLAIN (7) was in the money last start in fast time - poses a threat again.",
